task.summary: Removed test data, program now prints real sensor data.

Created a new Test Main, that can update the gui with received data. Old Main.java should be unmodified.
Created a Packet class that holds all of the weather data.
Added member to packet class, added new Arduino code with smaller packet size and a counter.

Added Arduino code to automatically gather data, then send it when connected for the first time. We use a boolean flag in Arduino to only send the complete data the first time. Maybe a more elegant solution is to have the java application send two different types of requests: One for a single packet (for normal polling) and one for an initial connection (Complete array of data).

Fixes a bug in Arduino code. timeStamp also holds the "packet number" for now (Makes the graph look nice.) We can probably improve by sending the timestep from the Arduino, and then have the Java program subtract the value of the first timestep from all successive packets, to get a better value.
